g.text: Never attended school or only kindergarten
95% confidence interval of average difference in height (cm)
Compared to a white, 18-64yrs, non-Hispanic woman with Year 12 education, household income $25k-$35k
The 'effects' of today's income and education are likely to actually be indicators of socioeconomic status while young,
impacting on both height and economic outcomes.
Income and education are related to height even after controlling for sex, age and race
Source: http://freerangestats.info analysis of the US CDC Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System Survey for 2018
